% layout 'default';
% title 'about';
<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="span1">&nbsp;</div>
	<div class="span7">
		<h1>about bkmrx.org</h1>
		<p>bkmrx.org is an open source project based on <a href="https://bkmrx.com/">bkmrx.com</a>, built purely in Perl,
		using the <a href="http://mojolicio.us/">Mojolicious</a> framework, <a href="http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/">Twitter Bootstrap</a>, 
		<a href="http://mongodb.org/">MongoDB</a> and the <a href="http://lucy.apache.org/">Lucy</a> search engine.</p>
		<h2>bookmarking is broken</h2>
		<p>bkmrx is a (small) attempt to bring online bookmarking into the 21<sup>st</sup> century. 
		bkmrx allows you to be the curator of your own search engine, and your own links. Unlike
		Google, Bing et al, you can define your own <a href="http://www.thefilterbubble.com/">filter bubble</a>.</p>
		<p>By open-sourcing bkmrx.org, many minds may be able to fix what delicious and others have so far failed 
		at doing.</p>
		<p>There are tons of great resources out there that may spark ideas for <a href="https://github.com/robhammond/bkmrx">contributing to bkmrx.org</a>:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><a href="https://blog.mozilla.org/ux/2012/10/save-for-later/">Save for later</a> - an excellent
			 user study conducted by Mozilla exploring the concept of 'save for later', and looking at various
			 potential solutions to the problem.</li>
		</ul>
		<h2>Comparison</h2>
		<p>Comparison with other bookmarking services:</p>
